n%20working%20hard%20to%20represent%20others%20in%20his%20community%20in%20red%20states.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJavier%20R.%20Quiroz%20Castro%20is%20a%20beneficiary%20of%20DACA%2C%20or%20Deferred%20Action%20for%20Childhood%20Arrivals%2C%20a%20policy%20introduced%20by%20the%20Obama%20administration%20in%202012%20that%20grants%20relief%20from%20deportation%20to%20undocumented%20immigrants%20brought%20to%20the%20country%20as%20children.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Quiroz%2C%2032%2C%20from%20near%20Houston%2C%20Texas%2C%20about%20pursuing%20a%20nursing%20career%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20come%20from%20a%20small%2C%20poor%20town%20in%20Mexico.%20They%20didn't%20see%20a%20future%20for%20me%20there%20and%20knew%20other%20people%20who%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20in%20search%20of%20a%20better%20life%2C%20so%20they%20decided%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-and-uk-life-biggest-differences-after-moving-home-space-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecame%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20I%20was%20three%20years%20old.%20We%20settled%20in%20Nashville%20because%20my%20parents%20had%20contacts%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20undocumented%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20it%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20my%20parents%20and%20I%20had%20to%20work%20very%20hard%20to%20earn%20a%20living%2C%20and%20we%20were%20always%20fearful%20of%20deportation.%20In%202013%2C%20at%2022%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20DACA%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaca-recipient-jaime-avalos-juarez-mexico-immigration-ice-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeferred%20action%20for%20childhood%20arrivals%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20was%20given%20a%20work%20