%20remember%20getting%20fingerprint%20and%20background%20checks%20done%20as%20part%20of%20the%20process%2C%20trusting%20the%20government%20with%20my%20information%20because%20they%20said%20they%20were%20going%20to%20protect%20me.%20It%20took%20six%20to%20eight%20months%20from%20my%20initial%20meeting%20with%20a%20lawyer%20to%20receiving%20my%20work%20authorization%20card%20in%20the%20mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20my%20nursing%20degree%20and%20license%20and%20moved%20to%20Houston%20with%20my%20wife%2C%20a%20US%20citizen%2C%20and%20also%20a%20nurse.%20We%20have%20two%20kids%20and%20a%20house%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Houston.%20We%20both%20currently%20work%20at%20a%20hospital%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20need%20to%20submit%20DACA%20renewals%20every%20two%20years%2C%20which%20means%20I%20can%20only%20plan%20my%20life%20in%20two-year%20increments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20become%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-became-us-citizen-through-naturalization-h1b-visa-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20citizen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hope%20to%20obtain%20legal%20status%20in%20the%20US%20through%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20announcement%20that%20some%20spouses%20of%20US%20citizens%20can%20apply%20for%20status%20without%20leaving%20the%20country%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20process%20requires%20me%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20and%20separate%20from%20my%20family%2C%20which%20is%20something%20I%20never%20wanted%20to%20do.%20There's%20the%20risk%20of%20something%20going%20wrong%20and%20not%20being%20allowed%20back%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0b95fd9-cffa-4bec-9427-450e61480f5f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20live%20in%20a%20red%20state%20and%20want%20to%20advocate%20for%20others%20who%20haven't%20received%20DACA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20one%20of%20the%20lucky%20ones%20who%20has%20benefited%20from%20DACA%2C%20but%20I%20know%20there%20are%20many%20others%20who%20haven't%20benefited.%20When%20I%20became%20a%20DACA%20recipient%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20prove%20Obama%20right%20and%20prove%20that%20Dreamers%20aren't%20bad%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20invited%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.govinfo.gov%2Fapp%2Fdetails%2FDCPD-202400534%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduce%20President%20Joe%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20an%20event%20in%20June%202024%20to%20mark%20the%2012th%20anniversary%20of%20DACA.%20Biden%20announced%20an%20executive%20order%20to%20help%20the%20spouses%20of%20US%20citizens%20obtain%20legal%20status.%20It%20was%20surreal.%20My%20wife%20and%20I%20met%20the%20President%2C%20who%20thanked%20us%20for%20our%20service%20as%20nurses.%20It%20was%20emotional%20to%20represent%20my%20people%20at%20the%20event%20and%20watch%20the%20President%20introduce%20an%20executive%20order%20for%20their%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-daca-reactions-backlash-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20administration%20tried%20to%20take%20DACA%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20fought%20hard%20to%20represent%20others%20in%20my%20community.%20I%20worked%20in%20nursing%20through%20the%20pandemic%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration%20and%20treated%20Trump%20supporters%20%E2%80%94%20I%20know%20that%20because%20I%20see%20the%20red%20hat%20in%20the%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20only%20lived%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-democrats-can-win-big-in-red-states-in-2024-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20have%20friends%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20political%20spectrum.%20When%20immigration%20comes%20up%20in%20conversation%2C%20some%20tell%20me%20they%20are%20OK%20with%20me%20but%20not%20with%20the%20people%20at%20the%20border.%20I%20remind%20them%20that%20my%20parents%20and%20I%20were%20once%20in%20that%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20administration%