0non-swim%20zones%2C%20provides%20logistical%20support%2C%20and%20assists%20lifesavers%20in%20making%20public%20safety%20announcements%20in%20multiple%20languages.%20It%20works%20alongside%20TRITON%20%E2%80%94%20an%20AI-driven%20monitoring%20system%20that%20offers%20comprehensive%20beach%20surveillance%2C%20spots%20tourists%20in%20distress%20in%20the%20water%20over%20long%20distances%2C%20and%20aids%20lifesavers%20in%20emergencies.%20Both%20AURUS%20and%20TRITON%20are%20currently%20deployed%20at%20Miramar%20beach%20in%20Panaji%20and%20operated%20by%20our%20%E2%80%98tech%20lifesavers%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EInside%20the%20lives%20and%20challenges%20of%20Goa%E2%80%99s%20lifeguards%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Drishti%20Marine%20became%20the%20custodian%20of%20beach%20safety%20in%20Goa%20in%202008%2C%20their%20lifeguards%20have%20rescued%20over%207%2C700%20people%2C%20including%20locals%2C%20and%20domestic%2C%20and%20international%20tourists%2C%20claims%20Rajiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20also%20trained%20responders%20for%20marine%20life%20strandings%2C%20working%20closely%20with%20the%20Forest%20Department%20and%20NGOs%20focused%20on%20marine%20welfare.%20A%20recent%20notable%20rescue%20occurred%20over%20the%20Independence%20Day%20weekend%20earlier%20this%20year%20when%20Drishti%20lifesavers%20(lifeguards)%20rescued%20nine%20fishermen%20after%20their%20boat%20capsized%20off%20Rajbagh%20Beach%20in%20South%20Goa%2C%20demonstrating%20their%20ability%20to%20handle%20mass%20rescues%20in%20extreme%20conditions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20goes%20on%20to%20add.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20professional%20training%20that%20the%20Drishti%20lifeguards%20receive%2C%20which%20saves%20them%20from%20many%20dangers%20associated%20with%20saving%20people%20from%20drowning%20at%20sea%2C%20the%20challenges%20they%20encounter%20are%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20Shashikant%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20people%20are%20drowning%2C%20they%20panic.%20When%20you%20directly%20engage%20with%20a%20victim%20of%20drowning%2C%20there%20is%20always%20the%20danger%20that%20they%E2%80%99ll%20drag%20you%20into%20the%20water%20with%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20lifeguards%2C%20we%20are%20told%20to%20first%20deploy%20a%20rescue%20tube%20or%20board%2C%20which%20the%20person%20drowning%20can%20hold%20on%20to%2C%20turn%20them%20towards%20the%20shore%2C%20clear%20up%20their%20airways%2C%20and%20push%20them%20towards%20the%20shore.%20But%20on%20occasions%20you%20come%20across%20drunk%20people%20who%20have%20swam%20too%20far%20off%20shore%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20get%20them%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20the%20rescue%20tube%20or%20board.%20With%20drunk%20people%2C%20we%20try%20to%20identify%20as%20many%20of%20them%20as%20possible%20and%20send%20out%20teams%20to%20evacuate%20them%20from%20the%20beach%20itself%2C%20or%20push%20them%20as%20far%20as%20away%20as%20possible%20from%20the%20shoreline.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwin%2C%20who%20claims%20to%20have%20done%20484%20rescues%20to%20date%2C%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CDespite%20having%20rescue%20equipment%2C%20a%20drowning%20person%E2%80%99s%20first%20instinct%20is%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20the%20rescuer%20because%20they%E2%80%99re%20in%20a%20state%20of%20panic.%20Also%2C%20there%20are%20occasions%20when%20the%20rip%20current%20is%20so%20strong%20that%20it%20takes%20six%20or%20seven%20people%20with%20it.%20This%20happens%20because%20one%20person%20tries%20to%20save%20the%20other%20but%20encounters%20strong%20rip%20currents.%20Handling%20these%20situations%20is%20challenging%20and%20you%20need%20more%20than%20one%20lifeguard%20and%20multiple%20equipment%20to%20save%20them.%20I%20was%20part%20of%20a%20rescue%20effort%20where%20we%20saved%20seven%20people%20at%20once.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fu1vobuGfnMo%3Fenablejsapi%3D1%26rel%3D0%26modestbranding%3D0%26autoplay%3D0%26cc_load_policy%3D0%26iv_load_policy%3D3%26loop%3D0%26fs%3D1%26playsinline%3D1%26controls%3D1%26color%3Dred%26cc_lang_pref%3D%26autohide%3D2%26theme%3Ddark%26%5C%22%20data-no-lazy%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20player%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwin%20also%20agrees%20that%20dealing%20with%20drunk%20people%20drowning%20at%20sea%20is%20challenging.%20%E2%80%9CSome%20of%20them%20are%20so%20drunk%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20realise%20that%20they%20have%20to%20get%20on%20top%20of%20a%20rescue%20board.%20Thanks%20to%20years%20of%20experience%20and%20training%2C%20we%20have%20learnt%20how%20to%20handle%20such%20situations.%20The%20trouble%20with%20drunk%20people%20is%20that%20sometimes%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20strength%20to%20get%20their%20torso%20on%20top%20of%20the%20rescue%20board.%20We%20have%20to%20help%20them%20get%20on%20top%20of%20the%20surfboard%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20before%20deploying%20the%20surfboard%20and%20pushing%20them%20up%20on%20the%20surfboard%2C%20we%20have%20to%20gauge%20the%20strength%20and%20movement%20of%20the%20waves%20and%20time%20our%20efforts%20properly.%20Now%2C%20if%20I%20jump%20into%20the%20water%20without%20timing%20it%20properly%2C%20the%20rescue%20board%20may%20get%20washed%20away%20onto%20the%20shore%20and%20then%20I%20have%20to%20push%20and%20carry%20the%20drowning%20person%20back%20without%20the%20rescue%20equipment.%20My%20job%20is%20to%20get%20the%20person%20who%20is%20drowning%20on%20top%20of%20the%20rescue%20board%20and%20drag%20them%20back%20to%20shore%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20training%2C%20Ashwin%20notes%20that%20there%20are%20occasions%20when%20the%20sea%20just%20overwhelms%20you%20with%20massive%20waves%20and%20strong%20currents.%20%E2%80%9CBesides%20these%20rip%20currents%2C%20you%20are%20also%20dealing%20with%20strong%20plunging%20waves%20that%20roll%20over%20victims%20of%20drowning.%20On%20these%20occasions%2C%20victims%20are%20often%20dragged%20200%20to%20400%20metres%20away%20from%20the%20shoreline.%20As%20trained%20lifeguards%2C%20we%20know%20how%20to%20swim%20and%20navigate%20past%20these%20plunging%20waves%20and%20rip%20currents.%20For%20tourists%2C%20however%2C%20if%20they%20get%20rolled%20under%20these%20massive%20plunging%20waves%2C%20they%20end%20up%20taking%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20seawater.%20In%20these%20scenarios%2C%20we%20have%20to%20deploy%20jet%20skis%20to%20rescue%20them%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20single-person%20rescue%2C%20we%20often%20use%20a%20rescue%20tube.%20If%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20than%20one%20person%2C%20we%20use%20a%20surf%2Frescue%20board.%20But%20our%20fastest%20equipment%20are%20jet%20skis%2C%20and%20these%20are%20particularly%20useful%20during%20the%20monsoon%20season%20when%20the%20rip%20currents%20are%20strongest%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShashikant%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnother%20challenge%20we%20encounter%20is%20uncooperative%20tourists%2C%20especially%20from%20foreign%20countries.%20When%20they%20visit%20Goa%20for%20the%20first%20time%20and%20see%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%2C%20they%20get%20the%20impression%20that%20the%20waters%20here%20are%20calm.%20What%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20realise%20is%20the%20power%20of%20strong%20rip%20currents%20in%20the%20Arabian%20Sea.%20Sometimes%2C%20we%20get%20into%20arguments%20with%20tourists%20and%20have%20to%20call%20the%20police%20to%20disperse%20them%20away%20from%20points%20where%20they%20can%20potentially%20drown.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20best%20efforts%2C%20however%2C%20there%20are%20rare%20occasions%20when%20people%20drown%20to%20death.%20How%20do%20lifeguards%20deal%20with%20this%20devastation%3F%20With%20a%20resigned%20look%20on%2C%20Shashikant%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20just%20human%2C%20and%20not%20gods.%20We%20do%20everything%20to%20save%20a%20life%20but%20sometimes%20God%20has%20other%20plans.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20why%20lifesaving%20is%20more%20than%20just%20a%20job%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20calling%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rajiv.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FDrishti-Marine-Rajiv-Somani-1727449328.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Drishti%20Marine%20chairperson%20Rajiv%20Somani%20on%20the%20left.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FDrishti-Marine-Rajiv-Somani-1727449328.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FDrishti-Marine-Rajiv-Somani-1727449328-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FDrishti-Marine-Rajiv-Somani-1727449328-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FDrishti-Marine-Rajiv-Somani-1727449328-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FDrishti-Marine-Rajiv-Somani-1727449328-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image